<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-10-01T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-10-01T07:00:00-05:00" n="126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.348 Z 4/47: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-01T13:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">October 1,
                                        1923—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 1—10:24
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>113. Department’s unnumbered instructions September 18th last. Minister
                            of Foreign Affairs states Belgian Government will grant desired
                            permission for passage of airship mentioned over Belgian territory.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>